        Div class "lnav"
            Div class "lbrand"
                Link "EPL" to "/"
            End
            Div class "lnav-right"
                Link "Docs" to "https://abneeshsingh21.github.io/EPL/"
                Link "Back to site" to "/"
                Div class "lnav-cta-wrap"
                    Link "Install" to "/#install"
                End
            End
        End
        Div class "legal"

            Div class "eyebrow"
                Text "Legal · Effective 16 June 2026"
            End
            Heading "Refund & Cancellation Policy"
            Div class "updated"
                Text "Last updated 16 June 2026"
            End
            Div class "intro"
                Text "This policy explains refunds and cancellations for paid offerings on the EPL website, such as sponsorships, support, or digital products. The EPL software itself is free and open-source under the Apache-2.0 license and is not a paid product."
            End
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "1. Digital nature of offerings"
            End
            Text "Paid offerings are digital goods or services. Because benefits may be delivered immediately or on a recurring basis, refunds are handled as described below."
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "2. Refund window"
            End
            Text "If you believe a charge was made in error, or you are not satisfied with a paid product, you may request a refund within 7 days of the transaction by emailing us with your transaction details."
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "3. Eligibility"
            End
            Text "Refunds are generally available in the following cases:"
            Div class "ul"
                Div class "li"
                    Text "Duplicate or accidental charges."
                End
                Div class "li"
                    Text "A paid product that was not delivered or could not be accessed."
                End
                Div class "li"
                    Text "A documented technical failure on our side that prevented use of the offering."
                End
            End
            Text "Voluntary sponsorships and donations are generally non-refundable once made, except in the error cases listed above."
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "4. How to request a refund"
            End
            Text "Email contact@eplang.me with the email address used for payment, the transaction or order ID, the date, the amount, and the reason for your request. We may ask for additional information to verify the transaction."
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "5. Processing of refunds"
            End
            Text "Approved refunds are issued to the original payment method through the original processor (Razorpay or Lemon Squeezy). Once approved, refunds typically appear within 5 to 10 business days, depending on your bank or payment provider."
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "6. Cancellations"
            End
            Text "Any recurring arrangement can be cancelled at any time to stop future charges. Cancellation prevents renewal but does not automatically refund the current period unless required by law."
            Div class "lh2"
                Text "7. Contact"
            End
            Div class "box"
                Text "For refund or cancellation requests, email contact@eplang.me."
            End

        End
        Div class "lfoot"
            Span class "c"
                Text "© 2024–2026 Abneesh Singh · EPL · Apache-2.0"
            End
            Div class "lfoot-links"
                Link "Terms" to "/terms"
                Link "Privacy" to "/privacy"
                Link "Refund" to "/refund"
                Link "Contact" to "mailto:contact@eplang.me"
            End
        End
    End
End

Route "/what-is-epl" shows
    Page "What is EPL? — The English Programming Language"
        Description "EPL (English Programming Language) is a real, open-source programming language whose syntax reads like plain English. Install it with pip install eplang."
        Stylesheet
                :root{--ink:#FFFFFF;--paper:#111113;--muted:#5F6066;--ink2:#2A2A2E;
